column5: I'm off to the bushes now!!!  You guys be good... if you can't be good, be careful    See ya's

Back from the bushes and happy to report, that our group got a nice 4 pointer, 118lbs field dressed  We had a mixture of rain, freezing rain and snow beginning of the week and below temps, dipping into -10C overnight and pretty steady there after  Glad I had my ground blind to battle the element    This bird wasn't too shy to perch on a branch close to the bind    Enjoy TJunkie
A young buck like that will be great eating. Good job!
Congrats on the Buck.
Congrats Jacques! Keep the tail for your summer fishing.
Mmmmmm, venison.
Nice looking steak there Jacques!  I mean Buck.. Ya, nice looking Buck
Thanks Skud!!!  You bet   Thanks K_F!!!   Thanks Roy!!!  Wish I'd of thought of it before it went to the butcher chop   Too late now   Yep  Thanks Chris!!!   LOL Nick... Thanks!!!
How could you? Really come on,a 4 point,,,,,,,,,,,,,,    LOL   Nice harvest my friend.
Did you get to bag one iFish4real??? If so... AWESOME   not yet this season but I'm after this guy
Thats a beast.  Look at the neck on that.   GOOD LUCK.
Thanks Brian!!!   Huge buck   Good luck

It's finally here folks... the day I've been waiting for   A quick update on our plans.... Last Wednesday afternoon, my brother went to our hunting grounds to drop 150LBS of carrots and to his surprise, the feeder had been cleaned right out    While he was dropping the food, got grunted by a buck     So all this to say that we are pumped to the max  Now I wait for him to pick me up... I'm as ready as I'll ever be    See you guys end of November TJunkie
nice! are you gonna be living in that cozy blind of yours?
This might come as a Shock to you Jacques,But deer season closes on the 18th.....  Good Luck with a Buck
Have a safe hunt, and hope you get a harvest.
Go get em Jacques!!  Remember to leave a couple for seed
good luck Jacques! harvest some bucks and get us a good report...
Dont forget extra batteries for the camera Jacques....expecting a video of success...  Safe hunt Cheers

You bet Christopher!!!  Now I must leave cause my brother is going to arrive any minutes now   No shock here Paul    Season ends on the 18th    Thanks will try my best   Thanks Brian!!!   Will do   Thanks Terrence!!!  Will do   Thanks gino!!!  Report to come I hope   Thanks Dave!!!  Batteries packed and ready  Brother's here now... must go... See you guys later
Good luck Jacques....at this rate you might be looking at another name change already
Good luck Jacques! But by the sounds of it you dont need it..
Good luck with the hunt bud. If you get skunked give a holler we can park you out on the front porch with a cup of coffee and a gun I bet even money the gun goes off before the coffee is cold.   Art
Neighbors that bad eh?
so that's what they mean by the buck stops here  good luck
No disrespect Jacques but I've never quite seen huntin' boots like those before.... and just one loaf a bread C'mon man!  Bon chasse!

*** Update *** Got back last night and sadly, opening weekend was a bust  Lots of fresh tracks all over but they are moving around at night     We had snow early morning and rain during the day... weather wise not quite cold enough.  I must say that I'm quite comfy in the blind and very happy to have it   Spent roughly 16 hours in it this weekend   Leaving again this up coming Friday for a whole week and just can't wait   Thanks Paul!!!   Thanks Simon!!! It's a possibility   Thanks Ron!!!   Thanks Art!!!   Sounds like you have lots of them around   Thanks Terry!!!   Thanks Grant!!!   The boots   I'd look pretty with those on eh     There's actually two loafs in the box
Forcast looks favorable for this up coming weekend Jac.Hope they come out to play with me.  Cold nights and warming to +2 for the day high.  Good luck.

Yes Brian, the forecast looks a lot better for the up coming weekend   Below zero overnight but just above during the day over this way too   That should get them moving and also going into the full rut.... one of them, is bound to do a stupid thing     such as stroll by and stopping to catch it's breath   MAN I just can't wait  Good luck to you too this weekend B

Wow too bad, still better then a good day workin thou isint it...lol My good friend nailed a 8 point buck tonight..just text messaged me pics from the bush..It was a double lung shot that dropped it right in its tracks..

You bet Ron    I'd much prefer put in 16 hours in the blind then work thats for sure   Awesome that your friend was able to bag an 8 pointer... well deserve high five from me  I still have a full week of hunting left... just hope I can set my sights on something like this... buck from my 2008 season... would make me very happy
lache pas la patate mon jaques!
I knew the one I shot had a twin brother
Merci Kevin!!! Il me reste encore une pleine semaine    Part Vendredi   Did you get to bag one iFish4real???  If so... AWESOME

Actually I have more deer than squirrels on the property the back 12 acres are all woods and brambles that we let grow out so the deer have food and shelter. The area I am in is Loudoun County Virginia and it has some of the highest deer populations in the USA. Besides around here all of my neighbors have guns and they will shoot back.lol.  Art
I kind of figured it was the case Art  If you don't hunt... better call your brother Joe
